type: web_research
title: fal.ai Video Generation Models - Complete Research for Japanese Manga Content
source: "Multiple fal.ai pages, pricing pages, and model documentation"
key_insights[14]: fal.ai hosts 600+ models including all major video generation models via unified API,"Wan 2.6 is cheapest at $0.05-0.15/sec with 9:16 support and up to 15 sec duration","Kling 3.0 is premium at $0.168-0.224/sec with 3-15 sec and 9:16 support",MiniMax Hailuo 2.3 has explicit anime/illustration style support at $0.045-0.08/sec,Grok Imagine Video has production-ready anime style support at ~$0.05/sec,Veo 3.1 supports 4K at $0.20-0.60/sec with image-to-video,"Luma Ray 2 supports 6 aspect ratios including 9:16 at $0.50/5sec","Pika v2.2 supports 9:16 at $0.20-0.45/video","HunyuanVideo is $0.40/video with 9:16 support (open source)",CogVideoX-5B supports portrait_16_9 at $0.20/video (open source),Stable Video Diffusion is cheapest at $0.075/video but limited quality,LTX Video 2.0 Pro supports 4K with audio at $0.06-0.24/sec,"For 1024x1024 input images, all models accept square input and can output any ratio",Japanese text rendering is generally weak across all video models - text burns into image before animation is recommended approach
findings[14]: "Wan 2.6: wan/v2.6/image-to-video - 720p/1080p, 5/10/15sec, 16:9/9:16/1:1/4:3/3:4, $0.10-0.15/sec","Kling 3.0 Std: fal-ai/kling-video/v3/standard/image-to-video - 3-15sec, 16:9/9:16/1:1, $0.168/sec (no audio)","Kling 3.0 Pro: fal-ai/kling-video/v3/pro/image-to-video - same but $0.224/sec","Hailuo 2.3 Pro: fal-ai/minimax/hailuo-2.3/pro/image-to-video - 1080p, ~$0.49/video, anime style support","Hailuo 02 Std: fal-ai/minimax/hailuo-02/standard/image-to-video - 768p $0.045/sec, 512p $0.017/sec","Grok Imagine: xai/grok-imagine-video/image-to-video - 480p/720p, $0.05/sec, anime-ready","Veo 3.1: fal-ai/veo3.1/image-to-video - 720p/1080p/4K, $0.20-0.60/sec","Veo 2: fal-ai/veo2 - 720p, 8sec max, $2.50/5sec","Luma Ray 2: fal-ai/luma-dream-machine/ray-2/image-to-video - 540p/720p/1080p, 5s/9s, $0.50/5sec","Pika v2.2: fal-ai/pika/v2.2/image-to-video - 720p/1080p, 5s/10s, $0.20-0.45","HunyuanVideo: fal-ai/hunyuan-video-image-to-video - 480p/720p, ~5sec, $0.40","CogVideoX-5B: fal-ai/cogvideox-5b/image-to-video - 512px default, $0.20","SVD: fal-ai/stable-video - 512px, $0.075, limited quality","LTX 2.0 Pro: fal-ai/ltxv-2/image-to-video - up to 4K, 6/8/10sec, $0.06-0.24/sec"
refs[8]: fal.ai/pricing - master pricing page,fal.ai/video - video model catalog,fal.ai/models/wan/v2.6/image-to-video/api - Wan 2.6 I2V endpoint,fal.ai/models/fal-ai/kling-video/v3/standard/image-to-video/api - Kling 3.0 I2V,fal.ai/models/fal-ai/minimax/hailuo-2.3/pro/image-to-video - Hailuo 2.3 I2V,fal.ai/models/xai/grok-imagine-video/image-to-video - Grok Imagine I2V,fal.ai/models/fal-ai/veo3.1/image-to-video - Veo 3.1 I2V,fal.ai/models/fal-ai/luma-dream-machine/ray-2/image-to-video/api - Luma Ray 2 I2V
recommendations[7]: "Tier 1 (Best Quality): Kling 3.0, Veo 3.1, Grok Imagine - for hero scenes","Tier 2 (Best Value): Wan 2.6, MiniMax Hailuo 2.3 - for bulk generation","Tier 3 (Budget): LTX Video 2.0, HunyuanVideo, CogVideoX - for testing","For manga/anime: MiniMax Hailuo 2.3 (explicit anime support) or Grok Imagine (proven anime workflow)","For 9:16 vertical: Wan 2.6, Kling 3.0, Pika v2.2, Luma Ray 2 all support it natively","For 1024x1024 square input: Most models accept square and will add motion within the frame","Recommended workflow: Burn Japanese text into source image first, then use image-to-video for subtle animation"
